description: From French déboucher (“to unblock, uncork; to finish; to culminate”), from dé- (“un-”) + boucher (“to block, stop”).

verbs.description: debouche (third-person singular simple present debouches, present participle debouching, simple past and past participle debouched)

entries.meaning: (military, of a body of soldiers) To enter into battle.
(hydrology, of a river or stream) To discharge into a larger body of water such as a lake or sea.
